You can send images in abase64 encoded format, too. For example:
# Download image and convert to base64 in one stepIMAGE_BASE64=$(curl-s"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/Correlation_coefficient.png"|base64-w0)# Send to OpenAI APIcurlhttps://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions\-H"Content-Type: application/json"\-H"Authorization: Bearer$OPENAI_API_KEY"\-d@-<<EOF
{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": [
        {"type": "text", "text": "What is in this image?"},
        {
          "type": "image_url",
          "image_url": { "url": "data:image/png;base64,$IMAGE_BASE64" }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
